HEADWORD: Corncrake
<hw>Corn"crake`</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocir⟧rn"kr⟦amac⟧k`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A bird (<spn>Crex crex</spn> or <spn>Crex
pratensis</spn>) which frequents grain fields; the European crake or
land rail; -- called also <altname>corn bird</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

